---
import Base from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const pdfUrl = "/downloads/capstone-evidence-pack.pdf";
---

<Base
  title="Capstone evidence pack (download)"
  description="Download or print the capstone evidence pack template — fill as you build your static site."
>
  <article class="lesson-sheet evidence-pack-page">
    <p class="type-label" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Capstone · Work-integrated</p>
    <h1>Evidence pack</h1>
    <p>
      You built skills across seven modules — the capstone is where you <strong>show them</strong>.
      Fill this pack as you go; submit it with your live URL. No essay required.
    </p>

    <div class="evidence-pack-actions">
      <a class="evidence-pack-actions__primary" href={pdfUrl} download>
        Download PDF
      </a>
      <button type="button" class="evidence-pack-actions__secondary" id="print-pack">
        Print this page
      </button>
    </div>

    <p class="evidence-pack-actions__hint">
      Same template as the <a href="/assessments/capstone">online capstone guide</a>.
      See the <a href="/reference/capstone-exemplar">filled exemplar</a> for what specific proof looks like.
      Assessors: see the <a href="/reference/capstone-assessor-rubric">assessor rubric</a>.
    </p>

    <section class="evidence-pack-print" id="evidence-pack-form" aria-label="Evidence pack form">
      <h2>Part A — Artefact</h2>
      <table class="evidence-pack-table">
        <tbody>
          <tr><th scope="row">Live URL</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field" aria-hidden="true"></span></td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Lighthouse Accessibility score</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field"></span></td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Date tested</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field"></span></td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Browser / Chrome version</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field"></span></td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Lighthouse mode</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field evidence-pack-field--short">Mobile / Desktop</span></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Part B — Row evidence</h2>
      <p>One specific line per row — where can an assessor verify on your live site?</p>
      <table class="evidence-pack-table">
        <tbody>
          <tr><th scope="row">Structure / UX</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field"></span></td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Accessibility</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field"></span></td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Visual design</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field"></span></td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Deployment</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field"></span></td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Content</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field"></span></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Part C — Brief</h2>
      <p>Attach your Module 06 one-page brief (Goal, Audience, Pages, Tone, Must-haves, Non-goals, Accessibility intent).</p>
      <div class="evidence-pack-brief-box" aria-hidden="true"></div>

      <h2>Part D — Work claims</h2>
      <table class="evidence-pack-table">
        <tbody>
          <tr><th scope="row">Hosting</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field"></span></td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Why this host (one line)</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field"></span></td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">AI used?</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field evidence-pack-field--short">Yes / No</span></td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">If yes — verified by hand</th><td><span class="evidence-pack-field"></span></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Submission checklist</h2>
      <ul class="evidence-pack-checklist">
        <li>Live URL loads in a fresh browser</li>
        <li>Lighthouse ≥ 90% on deployed URL</li>
        <li>All Part B rows have specific proof</li>
        <li>Brief attached (Part C)</li>
        <li>Part D complete</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <p style="margin-top: var(--space-xl);">
      <a href="/lessons/module-07/01">Capstone build workbook</a> ·
      <a href="/assessments/capstone">Full capstone guide</a>
    </p>
  </article>

  <script>
    document.getElementById("print-pack")?.addEventListener("click", () => window.print());
  </script>
</Base>
